The paper deals with a cognitive radio system with multiple users and interference, which involves topics related to information theory (cs.IT), network infrastructure (cs.NI), system and control theory (cs.SY), multimedia (cs.MM), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of optimization methods and relaying schemes also suggests a focus on mathematical optimization and signal processing, which are common in the cs.IT and cs.NI sub-categories.
